race.comment: ZALE (1) won two in a row in the country before getting a stitch chasing Watson at Canterbury last start. Better placed this time and in a field that has fallen away somewhat a return to form looks on the cards. SHOW BUSINESS (5) has been freshened up since making ground to finish fourth over 1200m here seven weeks ago. The wide gate doesn't look so bad now after all the scratchings. Finds a nice race and should be competitive. APOLLO RIDGE (4) went to the lead a long way out then tired late over this distance at the Kenso recently. Form prior to that at provincial level was hard. Should get a pretty good time of it up front and is perfectly placed to bounce back. JAEX (12) ran a cheeky race out in front when resuming over 1200m at Port Macquarie last start, tiring close to home to just miss the placings in a BM72 for the mares. Fitter for that run and is capable of giving backers a sight again. PRINCESS CRUIZER (11) is the best of the others.
